metadata.document_title: Creating a Next.js Project with `create-next-app`

__data__.text: This is a Next.js project bootstrapped with `create-next-app`.

metadata.document_title: Optimizing Geist Font and Setting Up Development Server in Next.js: A Comprehensive Guide

__data__.text:
Getting Started

First, run the development server:

```bash
npm run dev
# or
yarn dev
# or
pnpm dev
# or
bun dev
```

Open http://localhost:3000 with your browser to see the result.

You can start editing the page by modifying `app/page.tsx`. The page auto-updates as you edit the file.

This project uses `next/font` to automatically optimize and load Geist, a new font family for Vercel.

metadata.document_title: A Comprehensive Guide to Next.js: Documentation, Tutorials, and GitHub Repository

__data__.text:
Learn More

To learn more about Next.js, take a look at the following resources:

- Next.js Documentation - learn about Next.js features and API.
- Learn Next.js - an interactive Next.js tutorial.

You can check out the Next.js GitHub repository - your feedback and contributions are welcome!

metadata.document_title: Effortless Deployment with Vercel for Next.js Apps: A Comprehensive Guide

__data__.text:
Deploy on Vercel

The easiest way to deploy your Next.js app is to use the Vercel Platform from the creators of Next.js.

Check out our Next.js deployment documentation for more details.

Setting up Local Environment Variables in a Next.js Project

__data__.text:
# File: .env.local
# Directory: frontend (Next.js project root)
# Purpose: Local environment variables for front-end development

# === 🔑 Relay Agent API Key ===
# Used for authenticated control endpoints (if exposed)
NEXT_PUBLIC_RELAY_KEY=SupSnoop3636

# === 🌐 Backend API URL ===
# The base URL for all client-side API requests
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://fictional-space-xylophone-pj9q656569gwh6v45-8000.app.github.dev

# === Notes ===
# - Only variables prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are exposed to the browser.
# - Remove or override these in production via your hosting platform's env settings.
